<p><i><b>Smash Hits</b></i> was a pop music magazine, aimed at teenagers and young adults and originally published in the United Kingdom by <a href="EMAP" title="EMAP">EMAP</a>. It ran from 1978 to 2006 and was issued <a href="Fortnight" title="Fortnight">fortnightly</a> for most of that time. The name survives as a brand for a related <a href="Spin-off_(media)" title="Spin-off (media)">spin-off</a> <a href="Smash_Hits_(TV_channel)" title="Smash Hits (TV channel)">digital television channel</a>, <a href="Smash_Hits_Radio" title="Smash Hits Radio">digital radio station</a>, and website which have survived the demise of the printed magazine.</p>
